Text.Value: The world wakes to a new dawn, and we are here to greet it.
Freedom feels hollow. I regret not seizing control of the brain.
My name belongs to my mother, so our House will have a new name - your name - and the world will learn to fear it.
So am I, my love. Let us be monsters together.
I think you are wrong. Given what you have become, there is nothing we can not do together.
Not as conquerors, but as saviours.
With Gortash dead, Baldur's Gate needs new leadership.
I would have preferred to claim the whole world when we had the chance, but Baldur's Gate is not a bad place to start.
Why leave? We're heroes.
I know what is happening. The engine is failing. You are dying.
But despite everything we gave up when we destroyed the brain, it is good to be here with you.
You have endured so much, Karlach, and survived it all. You need not endure this pain in silence.
No higher power can command or restrain us - we will assemble an army of thralls, and who then will be able to stand against us?
Whatever we do, let's do it far from here.
Don't let it happen again.
Nobody should have that much power.
Nobody should have that much power.
All of your strength, all of your passion... all of your fire. Extinguished. Such a waste.
I should have taken control of the brain when I had the chance.
We deserved to rule.
Why would I ever leave?
We can put the Gondians back to work, rebuild the Steel Watch, and march on the Underdark with an unstoppable army at our back, and a song of conquest on our lips.
You're impossible. I love you. All right - let's go.
Concentrate. Try to contain the inferno threatening to consume you from within.
I was afraid I wouldn't be able to handle all of that power.
I was afraid I wouldn't be able to handle all of that power.
Perhaps it is time for my homecoming. An exile from Lolth and her mind flayer consort, leading a conquering horde on Menzoberranzan.
Good. We have faced so much together already - it is only right we test ourselves against an archdevil and her legions.
Come, my darling. We have a realm to conquer.
A shame to go to all the effort of saving the city if we do not seize it, but rebuilding will be a formidable task.
I thought your mind had evolved, not degraded. Do you not see? No matter our deeds, we both have the semblance of villains now.
It will be a glorious homecoming, and you will make a beautiful queen.
It will be a glorious homecoming, and you will make a beautiful king.
It will be a glorious homecoming, and you will make a beautiful monarch, ruling by my side.
We should visit your family in Menzoberranzan.
Do not presume you know what I do and don't deserve. I have chosen you - and I will have what is mine.
The people we saved will not thank us. They will hunt us, and kill us.
The engine can endure in Avernus - we can return there, together, and make Zariel regret ever laying eyes on you.
Doesn't it feel good to know that we did the right thing?
Where do you suggest we go?
I can't let you do that, Minthara. You deserve a better life than Avernus can offer.
I am a monster.
It would have felt like serving Bhaal again. I am free.
It would have felt like serving Bhaal again. I am free.
You do not ever need to be alone.
Your mind may be too powerful a thing for me to change, but I shall try.
I can't. I swore I'd never go back, and I meant it.
I am leaving, but not with you. We need to go our separate ways.
Whatever I am - whatever I become - I need to figure it out alone.
A moment of weakness.
A moment of weakness.
Yes, I would like that.
Now, I mourn the loss of the tadpole, because I can only imagine the wonders it could show me if our minds locked together as they once did.
We're heroes - let's enjoy the adulation of the people.
We reclaimed our freedom, though everything was against us. What would you do with it?
We can put the Gondians back to work, rebuild the Steel Watch, and march to Waterdeep with an unstoppable army at our back, and a song of conquest on our lips.
Whatever you cannot bear, I can take from you.
Our companions deserved to live.
Our companions deserved to live.
Perhaps you are right. This may be for the best.
In time, you will learn to master your form, and then you will be perfection.
The Sword Coast will be our battlefield, and Baldur's Gate will be the founding city of a new dynasty.
I want to go where you go.
No, Karlach. I will not lose you - not today.
You are infinite.
I will not let that happen. I hoped we might be able to enjoy the spoils of the city, but we must return to Avernus at once.
Would you have me navigate the hells without a guide?
The battle would be legendary, and our kingdom would be magnificent.
As do I. But smile, my love, there are yet more worlds to conquer. Perhaps it is time for my homecoming.
No, Minthara. I'm sorry. It's my time. All I want is to see the sky one last time before I go.
No.
Zariel is the last of your tormentors who lives. I will find her and punish her, whether you follow me or not.
Perhaps now we can make our own destiny.
Why did you not?
Stay with me one more day. Let me see all that you are, and I will show you what I believe we can be.
No more gods or monsters, no devils or demons to manipulate our fate.
Perhaps they still can be. Gratitude is an easy thing to exploit, and Baldur's Gate owes its continued existence to us.
Chult, Thay, Amn, Waterdeep... there is a world of wonders to discover, and boundless Realms to conquer.
I can think of one place that would be a natural home for us both.
Your body is gone, but your mind is more beautiful than ever. Before, I could hold all that you are in my thoughts.
I will never understand it, and I do not accept it. But if this is what you choose, I will stay with you until the end.
So you'll stay with me, and have a mind flayer as a consort?
Ugh, the people. They could have been our subjects if we had only seized power when we had the chance.
We can still conquer using our own strength. For us - not for Bhaal.
We can still conquer using our own strength and wits.
We will make Zariel sorry she ever laid eyes on you.
Yes, that would be good. I'm sure my mother has missed me - she likes competition.
But we can look to the future tomorrow... or the day after. Today, let us think only of ourselves in this moment. We have won a lifetime together.
All right - if you're by my side, I can bear it.
Saviours of a city that we must now leave forever.
I'm sorry - I should have taken control of the brain.
I think there's only one road left for me to travel. My engine's cooked. It's time.
*Your engine screeches and grinds within your chest; the inferno is here - and there's no holding it back.*
After all that we have done together, you would leave me now?
The world wakes to a new dawn, and we are here to greet it.

EditorData.NodeContext: Bittersweet parting of ways between Halsin and his lover, who transformed into a mind flayer in order to save the world.

Text.Value: You even more than I.
Not as conquerors, but as saviours.

Synopsis:
Player and Minthara wake up in a private room at the Elfsong tavern, having spent the night together after saving the city and destroying the netherbrain. 

Minthara is a little bit upset that the player didn't seize control of the brain and become the new Absolute, but she's in love with them and forgives them. And then dreams about their next conquests.
